text.section:
In the examination for a permit of competence:
The examining authority shall give the examination;
The applicant shall pay the examining authority a $1 examination fee for each examination taken;
At the discretion of the examining authority, the examination may be oral or written. If the examination is oral, it shall be reduced to writing and filed among the examining authority's records;
The examination shall include practical mining questions relating to ventilation and the methods of detecting noxious and explosive gas in a mine;
The applicant shall demonstrate to the examining authority that he is qualified to supervise the operation of a small mine;
If the applicant fails the examination, he may request another examination after 60 days from the unsuccessful examination and the examining authority shall conduct another examination as soon as practicable; and
The examining authority shall issue a "permit of competence" if the applicant is found qualified. No applicant may be required to display the theoretical knowledge required for the holder of a first-class certificate. He shall be qualified in the practicable aspects of conditions relating to the safety of the employees of this type mine.
